# Hamshack Dashboard – UI Concept

When adding or changing UI (client/src, styles.css), **always follow the existing UI concept** so the app stays consistent.

## Layout

- **Topbar:** Callsign, locator/QTH line, tagline | Settings button, Next contest (if any), Clock (UTC, local, sun times, grayline).
- **Main:** Sidebar (tabs + one content area) + Map. Sidebar tabs: News, Contests, DXped, Band, Space, Weather, MUF, Spots, PSK, Sat.
- **One-page sidebar:** No separate “pages”; one tablist and one scrollable content area. Active tab decides which panel is visible.

## Panel Pattern

- Every panel lives in a **`.panel`** with a clear **`<h2>`** heading.
- **Loading:** Use **`PanelLoading`** (skeleton lines).
- **Error:** Use **`PanelError`** with message and Retry.
- **Empty state:** Use **`.panel-empty`** (or **`.panel-empty-inline`** inside cards). Same copy style (muted, 13px).
- **Content layout:** Prefer **`.panel-content-grid`** (display: grid, gap: 10px) for panels with filters + content.

## List / Slider Pattern

- **Card:** **`.news-slider-card`** (rounded, subtle border, min-height).
- **Content link/block:** **`.news-slider-link`** (flex column, padding). Use for clickable items or static blocks.
- **Title:** **`.news-slider-title`**; **`.news-slider-date`** for secondary text; **`.news-slider-hint`** for “Read more” style.
- **Navigation:** **`.news-slider-nav`** with **`.news-slider-nav-row`**: prev button, **`.news-slider-counter`** (e.g. 1 / 5), next button. Use **`news-slider-btn`** for prev/next. Nav as **sibling below** the card (never inside). Support arrow keys (tabIndex, onKeyDown).
- Use this same pattern for News, Contests, DXpeditions, Spots, Satellites (one “item” at a time, optional carousel).

## Filter Toggles

- **Toggle group:** **`.contests-toggle`** / **`.dxpeditions-toggle`** with **`.contests-toggle-btn`** / **`.dxpeditions-toggle-btn`**. Active state: **`.active`** (blue tint). Use **role="group"** and **aria-label**.
- **Spots:** **`.spots-filters`** with **`.spots-filter`** (label + select) and optional checkbox (e.g. Reachable). Same compact row, same background/border.

## Map

- **Toolbar:** **`.hf-prop-bar`** (flex, wrap). Buttons/inputs use shared styles; layer toggles can use **`.map-ctrl-btn`**.
- **Legend:** **`.map-legend`** container, **`.map-legend-box`** per block, **`.map-legend-title`**, **`.map-legend-row`**, **`.map-legend-item`**, **`.map-legend-dot`**, **`.map-legend-label`**. Prefer these classes over inline styles for new legend content.

## Theming & Focus

- **Colors:** Use CSS variables (--bg, --panel, --text, --muted, --line). Accent blue **rgba(77,171,247,…)** for active/links.
- **Focus:** Every interactive element must have a clear **:focus-visible** style (outline or box-shadow). Sidebar tabs, buttons, selects, map controls.
- **Accessibility:** **aria-label** on icon-only or ambiguous controls. **aria-pressed** for toggle buttons. **role="tablist"** / **role="tab"** for sidebar.

## Consistency Rules

1. **No one-off layouts:** New panels use the same card/slider or filter+content pattern as existing ones.
2. **Centralise styles:** Prefer classes in **styles.css** over inline styles. Reuse **.panel-empty**, **.news-slider-***, **.map-legend-***, etc.
3. **Callsigns:** Use **CallsignLink** (or link to QRZ) for callsigns so behaviour is consistent.
4. **English:** All user-facing strings in English.

When in doubt, mirror an existing panel (e.g. Contests or DXpeditions) for structure and classes, then adapt content.
